. The new species shares the same species of host with 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6A380EFEF7FD21FDE8FCC8" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[306,557,751,777]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Adrodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tectifera" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFEF7FD21FDE8FCC8" box="[306,557,751,777]" italics="true" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">Adrodelphys tectifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6A380EFDFBFD21FCCFFCC8" bold="true" box="[574,778,751,777]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED6A380EFDFBFD21FCCFFCC8" box="[574,778,751,777]" pageId="571" pageNumber="572" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(described below) from the same locality.
</paragraph>
